result.execSummary:
The defendant Johnathan L Barrett was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Def in person & by Atty Mike Kenitz.  Atty Sandra Jo Giernoth appeared for State.  Clerk: CP.   State moves to dismiss and read-in Ct 3; Court so orders. Statements from State, counsel and def.  Court proceeds to sentencing.
Hearing at 08-07-2015 10:30 am

Def in person & by Atty Mike Kenitz.  Atty Peter John Cannon appeared for State.  Clerk: CP.  Court questions State.  Statements from counsel.  Court reviews amended Information w/def.  Counsel expects case to resolve w/joint agreement except for argument re length of probation.  Counsel req separate sentencing date - def to report immediately upon entering plea.  Hearing scheduled for August 7, 2015 at 10:30 am.
Juror Selection and Peremptory Challenges
Hearing at 07-28-2015 09:00 am

Def in person & by Atty Mike Kenitz.  Atty Mandy A. Schepper appeared for State.  Clerk: CP.  Case called 8:18am w/out jury.  Discussion re witnesses.  Def wishes to enter plea to Ct 1 w/sentencing adj pending outcome of trial re Ct 2 (no agreement). Def enters guilty plea to Ct 1.  Court finds def guilty on Ct 1.  Discussion re Ct 2 and trial.  Def acknowledges prior OWI convictions.  Discussion re status of def's DL.  Court finds any reference to operating of def's motor vehicle after revocation is irrelevant.  State indicates one juror did not provide any info on juror questionnaire - per jury clerk, info not required.  Recess.  Reconvene.  Discussion re one of State's witnesses.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present at 8:41am.  Jury panel sworn.  20 jurors called to box.  Voir dire by Court.  Voir dire by counsel.  Jurors struck.  12 juror names called; remaining jurors thanked and released at 9:19am.  Jury sworn.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury present.  Atty Kenitz moves for sequestration of witnesses; Court will so order w/exception of Officer and expert.  Discussion re stipulation (exh #6); Court questions def and finds def knowingly, freely and voluntarily stipulated to chain of custody.  Discussion re testimony of expert not being same who tested blood; Atty Kenitz objects - Court overrules and will allow testimony.  State has altered one exhibit; def does not object.  Jury now present.  Preliminary jury instructions given by Court.  Opening statements.  WITNESS:  Officer J Otte (WBPD).  Court has sidebar w/counsel.   Jury excused.  Atty Kenitz objects to testimony of officer re PBT; counsel moves to strike testimony and moves for mistrial.  Argument from State.  Court takes objection under advisement at this time and reserves right of counsel to make objection at later time if def found guilty by jury.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury present.  Atty Kenitz moves again for mistrial; Court grants motion.  Jury present.  Court provides explanation of mistrial to jury and releases jurors at 10:37am.  State/counsel req further proceedings be set.  Hearing scheduled for July 28, 2015 at 09:00 am.
